lass=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span> Cura\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">tores\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Q(uintus) Mac\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ulnius\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Ṭ(itus) Trụt\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">tedi\u003C/span>[us \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>A(ulus) Turiu\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">s\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan class=\"underline\">A\u003C/span>(uli) \u003Cspan class=\"underline\">OCHAC\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Alex Antoniou, Robert Crellin\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>CURA\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">TORES\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>QMAC\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">ULNIUS\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>.TR.T\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">TEDI\u003C/span>[..\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ATURIU\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">S\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">A\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">OCHAC\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000285_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo Liceo Lazzaro 2017-11-18\" src=\"ISic000285_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000285.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo Liceo Lazzaro 2017-11-18\" src=\"ISic000285-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Korhonen 2004\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Curators Quintus Maculnius, Titus Truttedius, Aulus Turius, son of Aulus\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Only the left half of the text is preserved, compared to the earlier antiquarian records. The reading is extremely difficult, due to the nature of the volcanic stone, as noted already by Gualtherus. Modern repainting of the letters, seemingly following the reading of Gualtherus' second edition, only confuses the issue, rather than providing certainty (e.g. the painting of an A in line 3 appears to be without foundation on the stone). The text would appear to be of early (i.e. Augustan) date, reflecting construction of the aqueduct around the foundation of the Roman colonia.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 273 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones